  <summary date="2015-09-10T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Adjusting Davis-Bacon for Inflation Act

 Increases from $2,000 to $50,000 the contract threshold requiring the locally prevailing wage rate to be paid to various classes of laborers and mechanics working under federally-financed or federally-assisted contracts for construction, alteration, and repair of public buildings or public works (Davis-Bacon Act).</summary>
